# TikTok Academy Lesson Author

## What this skill is for

Writing the `Lesson` field body HTML for any record in the **Lessons** table (`gFW6PZeT2JHVCk`) in the **Content Tracking App** database. The React lesson block (`tiktok-academy/lessons/page-structure-v3.jsx`) renders this field as scoped HTML inside a `.lesson-prose` wrapper and styles everything via CSS. That means your HTML must be plain, semantic, and whitelist-compliant — all visual styling happens in the block, not the database.

Do NOT embed inline styles, `<style>` tags, `<script>` tags, or Canva `<iframe>` wrappers. If you do, the lesson will look wrong and future design updates will be painful.

## Where each piece of lesson content lives

Before writing HTML, know which field holds what. Do not duplicate content across fields.

| Content | Field | Type | ID |
|---|---|---|---|
| Lesson title | `Name` | SINGLE_LINE_TEXT | `4e8yM` |
| Lesson number ("Lesson 1") | `Lesson Number` | SINGLE_LINE_TEXT | `42btG` |
| Category (SHOP/LIVE/ORGANIC/PLATFORM) | `Category` | SELECT | `jXSnc` |
| Difficulty | `Difficulty` | SELECT | `5khor` |
| Short description (hero paragraph) | `Description` | LONG_TEXT | `ck1JJ` |
| Duration ("30:00") | `Duration` | SINGLE_LINE_TEXT | `VB4oU` |
| **Lesson body HTML** | **`Lesson`** | **LONG_TEXT** | **`0wTBQ`** |
| Canva video embed URL | `Explainer` | URL | `DqSLD` |
| Podcast audio file (listen on the go) | `Podcast` | ATTACHMENT | `uU6oS` |
| Slide deck download (optional) | `Slides` | ATTACHMENT | `nINLz` |
| Linked Course | `Course` | LINKED_RECORD → Course | `v5YZr` |

**Do not** put the Canva video iframe inside the `Lesson` body — the block renders it from the `Explainer` URL. **Do not** upload the podcast into the lesson body — it's a separate audio asset. **Do not** store the TOC anywhere; the block auto-derives section navigation from `<h2 id="sec-N">` headings in the body at render time (a dedicated TOC sidebar is not rendered — sections are used only for scroll-tracking and the optional "resume where you left off" feature).

## Tag whitelist

Use only these tags in the `Lesson` body. Anything else will be stripped or misrender.

### Section headings
```html
<h2 id="sec-1">First section title</h2>
<h2 id="sec-2">Second section title</h2>
```
- IDs must be sequential starting at `sec-1`. No gaps. No other IDs. The lesson block uses these for scroll-spy and resume progress.
- No `<h1>`, no `<h3>`–`<h6>`. Only `<h2>` for sections.

### Paragraphs and inline formatting
```html
<p>Body copy. Emphasis goes in <strong>bold</strong> or <em>italic</em>. Link out with <a href="https://example.com">a plain anchor</a>.</p>
```
- Allowed inline tags: `<strong>`, `<em>`, `<a href="…">`.
- No inline `style="…"` attributes anywhere.
- No `<br>` — use separate `<p>` blocks.

### Lists
```html
<ul>
  <li>Unordered item</li>
  <li>Another one</li>
</ul>

<ol>
  <li>Step one</li>
  <li>Step two</li>
</ol>
```

### Slide images (Cloudinary)
```html
<img class="lesson-slide" src="https://res.cloudinary.com/dmrekfwpj/image/upload/f_auto,q_auto/tiktok-academy/shop/lesson-01/slides/slide-02.png" alt="" />
```
- Slides live **inline in the HTML** next to the paragraphs that explain them. They are not stored in a separate field.
- One slide per section is the usual pattern: put the `<img>` directly after the `<h2>`, before the paragraphs.
- Always include `class="lesson-slide"` and `alt=""` (or a short alt if the image carries information the body copy doesn't).
- Use Cloudinary URLs with `f_auto,q_auto` transforms so the block can resize them responsively. Folder convention: `tiktok-academy/<category>/lesson-NN/slides/slide-XX.png`.
- No `width`, `height`, `style`, `loading`, or any other attributes.

### Callouts (optional)
```html
<div class="callout">
  <p>This is a highlighted insight, definition, or warning. Use sparingly — once or twice per lesson at most.</p>
</div>
```
- A `<div class="callout">` wraps one or more `<p>` blocks that should render as a pulled-out box.
- No other classes. No nested callouts.

### Quizzes (inline, optional)
```html
<div class="quiz" data-question="What percentage of TikTok Shop revenue comes from creators with under 50K followers?">
  <div>20%</div>
  <div>50%</div>
  <div data-correct="true">80%</div>
  <div>95%</div>
</div>
```
- The question goes on the container via `data-question="…"`. Keep it to one sentence.
- Each answer is a direct child `<div>` with the answer text as plain text.
- Mark exactly one answer with `data-correct="true"`.
- 3–5 answers. Keep them short.
- There is no scoring and no storage — quizzes are just in-lesson self-checks. The block re-renders these divs as styled cards and reveals the correct answer on click.

## Structural rules for a whole lesson body

1. **Optional intro paragraph** at the very top, before any `<h2>`. Use this to tell the reader what they're about to watch/read and how to work through the lesson. Keep it short.
2. **Sections** follow the intro. Each section is:
   - `<h2 id="sec-N">Title</h2>`
   - optional `<img class="lesson-slide" …>` immediately after the heading
   - one or more `<p>` blocks explaining the slide / delivering the teaching
   - optional `<ul>` / `<ol>` / `<div class="callout">` / `<div class="quiz">` mixed in where they belong
3. Sections are numbered **sequentially** (`sec-1`, `sec-2`, `sec-3`, …). Do not skip numbers. Do not reuse numbers across lessons — each lesson starts at `sec-1` again.
4. **No horizontal rules, no tables, no blockquotes, no code blocks.** If you need to emphasise something, use a callout.
5. **No emoji used for UI purposes.** Emoji inside body copy is fine when it's part of the voice, but don't use ✓ ✗ ▶ ⭐ etc. as visual indicators — the block handles those with CSS.
6. **Never paste Canva iframes.** The video embed comes from the `Explainer` URL field. If you find yourself copying `<iframe src="https://www.canva.com/…">`, that URL belongs in `Explainer`, not in the body.

