## Authoring workflow

When asked to write a new lesson body from a Canva slide PDF or outline:

1. **Know the category and lesson number** up front (SHOP / LIVE / ORGANIC / PLATFORM, Lesson N). These determine the Cloudinary folder path for slides (`tiktok-academy/<category>/lesson-NN/slides/…`).
2. **Decide on the section breakdown first.** Read the outline, group the slides into topical sections, and draft the `<h2>` titles before writing any body copy. Aim for 8–15 sections per lesson.
3. **Draft each section** as: heading → slide image → 1–3 paragraphs → optional list/callout/quiz.
4. **Add quizzes sparingly.** Use them to check one concrete fact per section; not every section needs one. A 14-section lesson with 4–6 quizzes feels right.
5. **Validate the output** before pasting into Softr:
   - No `style="` attributes anywhere.
   - No `<style>`, `<script>`, `<iframe>`, `<table>`, `<blockquote>`, `<details>`, `<summary>`, `<br>`, or `<h1>/<h3>/<h4>/<h5>/<h6>` tags.
   - Every `<img>` has `class="lesson-slide"` and an `alt` attribute.
   - Every `<div class="quiz">` has `data-question` and exactly one child marked `data-correct="true"`.
   - Section IDs are `sec-1`, `sec-2`, … sequential, no gaps.
6. **Paste into the `Lesson` field** of the target record in Softr. Nothing else changes.

## What NOT to do — common mistakes

- ❌ Copying a Canva block with the iframe wrapper. The iframe URL belongs in `Explainer`.
- ❌ Adding inline colours (`style="color:#294ff6"`) to match the brand palette. Brand colours are applied by the block's CSS — raw HTML should be uncoloured.
- ❌ Using `<div>` with custom classes to build layouts. The only allowed classes are `lesson-slide`, `callout`, `quiz`, and the `data-*` attributes on `.quiz` children.
- ❌ Putting the TOC in the body. There is no TOC field and no TOC render in v3 — delete any `<nav>`, `<ul class="toc">`, etc.
- ❌ Putting the podcast link in the body. The block renders the `Podcast` attachment as a dedicated player card above the lesson body.
- ❌ Using `<details>` / `<summary>` for quizzes. The block re-renders `.quiz` divs as styled cards — using native `<details>` breaks this.
- ❌ Uploading the same slide twice because you forgot to number the Cloudinary files. Slides are numbered `slide-02`, `slide-03`, … (slide-01 is usually the cover, which the block doesn't show).
- ❌ Writing a lesson with no `<h2 id="sec-N">` sections at all. The block assumes sections exist for scroll tracking.

